WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.380 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.380 --> 00:00:12.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Easter Island statues
could hold the secret of what

00:00:12.170 --> 00:00:16.329 align:middle line:84%
happened in the world
before history began.

00:00:16.329 --> 00:00:19.870 align:middle line:84%
Why did ancient cultures with
no known contacts have so much

00:00:19.870 --> 00:00:22.830 align:middle line:90%
in common?

00:00:22.830 --> 00:00:26.970 align:middle line:84%
My theory is, they all
derived from a common source,

00:00:26.970 --> 00:00:29.370 align:middle line:90%
a single lost civilization.

00:00:29.370 --> 00:00:32.346 align:middle line:90%


00:00:32.346 --> 00:00:34.826 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:34.826 --> 00:01:04.099 align:middle line:90%


00:01:04.099 --> 00:01:07.640 align:middle line:84%
Almost 600 myths collected
on every continent

00:01:07.640 --> 00:01:09.950 align:middle line:84%
speak of a global
flood that swept away

00:01:09.950 --> 00:01:13.890 align:middle line:90%
an advanced civilization.

00:01:13.890 --> 00:01:17.550 align:middle line:84%
This is the basis of
the Noah's Ark story.

00:01:17.550 --> 00:01:19.500 align:middle line:84%
I believe that
such stories record

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:24.350 align:middle line:84%
real events that shook the earth
at the end of the last ice age.

00:01:24.350 --> 00:01:28.510 align:middle line:84%
The myths say there were
survivors, ancient mariners,

00:01:28.510 --> 00:01:31.767 align:middle line:84%
who rode out the flood in great
ships and colonized new lands.

00:01:31.767 --> 00:01:41.220 align:middle line:90%


00:01:41.220 --> 00:01:45.180 align:middle line:84%
Easter Island today is just a
tiny, windswept volcanic peak,

00:01:45.180 --> 00:01:48.180 align:middle line:84%
protruding above the almost
limitless wastes of the Pacific

00:01:48.180 --> 00:01:49.350 align:middle line:90%
Ocean.

00:01:49.350 --> 00:01:51.630 align:middle line:84%
But before the end
of the last ice age,

00:01:51.630 --> 00:01:53.760 align:middle line:90%
things were very different.

00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:57.180 align:middle line:84%
Sea levels were almost
400 feet lower then.

00:01:57.180 --> 00:01:59.880 align:middle line:84%
And an observer
sitting here, instead

00:01:59.880 --> 00:02:02.780 align:middle line:84%
of seeing endless
wastes of ocean,

00:02:02.780 --> 00:02:05.850 align:middle line:84%
would have seen a vista of
valleys and mountain peaks,

00:02:05.850 --> 00:02:07.710 align:middle line:84%
stretching away
towards the horizon.

00:02:07.710 --> 00:02:12.680 align:middle line:90%


00:02:12.680 --> 00:02:15.860 align:middle line:84%
Around 13,000 years ago,
the melting ice sheets

00:02:15.860 --> 00:02:18.108 align:middle line:84%
unleashed a catastrophic
flood upon the earth.

00:02:18.108 --> 00:02:20.800 align:middle line:90%


00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:25.240 align:middle line:84%
Historians dispute the myths
of an advanced civilization.

00:02:25.240 --> 00:02:27.370 align:middle line:84%
They tell us there were
only primitive tribes

00:02:27.370 --> 00:02:29.900 align:middle line:90%
of hunter gatherers then.

00:02:29.900 --> 00:02:34.670 align:middle line:84%
No agriculture, no architecture,
no writing, no cities,

00:02:34.670 --> 00:02:39.300 align:middle line:84%
and certainly no
advanced civilization.

00:02:39.300 --> 00:02:41.970 align:middle line:84%
Yet, if such a
civilization had existed,

00:02:41.970 --> 00:02:47.160 align:middle line:84%
its ruins would be under
water, completely out of sight.

00:02:47.160 --> 00:02:50.601 align:middle line:84%
My quest is to look for the
traces of its survivors.

00:02:50.601 --> 00:02:56.260 align:middle line:90%


00:02:56.260 --> 00:02:59.620 align:middle line:84%
Surrounded by the deeps
of the Pacific Ocean,

00:02:59.620 --> 00:03:03.470 align:middle line:84%
Easter Island is a
mystery made of statues.

00:03:03.470 --> 00:03:06.650 align:middle line:84%
Almost 1,000 of them,
weighing dozens of tons each,

00:03:06.650 --> 00:03:08.770 align:middle line:84%
distributed all
around the island.

00:03:08.770 --> 00:03:14.640 align:middle line:90%


00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:17.100 align:middle line:84%
For hundreds of years,
they were quarried here

00:03:17.100 --> 00:03:19.980 align:middle line:84%
in Rano Raraku, hewn
out of the living

00:03:19.980 --> 00:03:22.640 align:middle line:90%
rock in this great crater rim.

00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:25.540 align:middle line:84%
And then suddenly, for
no apparent reason,

00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:26.410 align:middle line:90%
the work stopped.

00:03:26.410 --> 00:03:29.310 align:middle line:84%
It's as though the artisans
just downed their tools,

00:03:29.310 --> 00:03:33.270 align:middle line:84%
and went away, and never
came back to it again.

00:03:33.270 --> 00:03:36.720 align:middle line:10%
Archaeologists see it all
as a great folly, which

00:03:36.720 --> 00:03:39.390 align:middle line:10%
came to an end as follies do.

00:03:39.390 --> 00:03:41.920 align:middle line:90%
But the ancients weren't stupid.

00:03:41.920 --> 00:03:43.870 align:middle line:84%
And they didn't do
all this for nothing.

00:03:43.870 --> 00:03:48.720 align:middle line:90%


00:03:48.720 --> 00:03:51.030 align:middle line:84%
For a start, the
sculptures are rooted

00:03:51.030 --> 00:03:52.680 align:middle line:84%
in astronomy, which
would have been

00:03:52.680 --> 00:03:54.780 align:middle line:84%
an essential tool for
the navigators who

00:03:54.780 --> 00:03:57.850 align:middle line:90%
first found this place.

00:03:57.850 --> 00:04:00.850 align:middle line:84%
The giant statues and the
platforms they stand on

00:04:00.850 --> 00:04:03.970 align:middle line:84%
face the rising sun on
specific days of the year,

00:04:03.970 --> 00:04:05.540 align:middle line:84%
and target the
significant stars.

00:04:05.540 --> 00:04:09.890 align:middle line:90%


00:04:09.890 --> 00:04:11.960 align:middle line:84%
It was part of a
massive endeavor

00:04:11.960 --> 00:04:14.480 align:middle line:90%
to connect sky to ground.

00:04:14.480 --> 00:04:16.940 align:middle line:84%
And it's a pattern I'm seeing
all over the ancient world.

00:04:16.940 --> 00:04:20.269 align:middle line:90%


00:04:20.269 --> 00:04:22.190 align:middle line:84%
But there's no
evidence whatsoever

00:04:22.190 --> 00:04:24.360 align:middle line:84%
of any contact between
these early cultures.

00:04:24.360 --> 00:04:27.540 align:middle line:90%


00:04:27.540 --> 00:04:30.090 align:middle line:84%
2,000 miles from
anywhere, Easter Island

00:04:30.090 --> 00:04:32.640 align:middle line:84%
is the remotest inhabited
spot in the world.

00:04:32.640 --> 00:04:36.510 align:middle line:90%


00:04:36.510 --> 00:04:40.170 align:middle line:84%
Yet it emerges from legend
as a place of refuge,

00:04:40.170 --> 00:04:42.210 align:middle line:84%
for the survivors of
a terrible flood that

00:04:42.210 --> 00:04:43.650 align:middle line:84%
had destroyed the
earth at the end

00:04:43.650 --> 00:04:45.360 align:middle line:90%
of a prehistoric golden age.

00:04:45.360 --> 00:04:54.240 align:middle line:90%


00:04:54.240 --> 00:04:56.670 align:middle line:84%
The only real event
that fits the bill

00:04:56.670 --> 00:04:59.640 align:middle line:84%
is the sudden end of the last
ice age, when melting ice

00:04:59.640 --> 00:05:00.830 align:middle line:90%
caps flooded the globe.

00:05:00.830 --> 00:05:06.150 align:middle line:90%


00:05:06.150 --> 00:05:08.490 align:middle line:84%
Many coastal areas which
could have supported

00:05:08.490 --> 00:05:10.436 align:middle line:84%
an advanced seagoing
civilization

00:05:10.436 --> 00:05:12.102 align:middle line:84%
would have been
inundated and the people

00:05:12.102 --> 00:05:14.070 align:middle line:90%
forced to find new homes.

00:05:14.070 --> 00:05:18.510 align:middle line:90%


00:05:18.510 --> 00:05:21.750 align:middle line:84%
>> The geological record
is fairly well established,

00:05:21.750 --> 00:05:25.920 align:middle line:84%
that around the 11th,
12th, 13th millennium,

00:05:25.920 --> 00:05:30.540 align:middle line:84%
something cataclysmic happened
over the face of the Earth.

00:05:30.540 --> 00:05:34.380 align:middle line:10%
The ice melted, producing
tremendous climatic changes.

00:05:34.380 --> 00:05:39.190 align:middle line:10%
There were enormous
earthquakes all over the place.

00:05:39.190 --> 00:05:43.510 align:middle line:84%
Many, many animals of
the Ice Age went extinct.

00:05:43.510 --> 00:05:46.870 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly, the sea levels
rose precipitously,

00:05:46.870 --> 00:05:49.705 align:middle line:84%
100 meters within
the space of days.

00:05:49.705 --> 00:05:52.710 align:middle line:90%


00:05:52.710 --> 00:05:54.640 align:middle line:84%
So when you put all
of this together,

00:05:54.640 --> 00:05:57.990 align:middle line:84%
you have a scenario and a
very well-established, deeply

00:05:57.990 --> 00:06:03.930 align:middle line:84%
scientific, geological scenario
for dramatic earth changes

00:06:03.930 --> 00:06:05.730 align:middle line:84%
everywhere over the
face of the planet.

00:06:05.730 --> 00:06:13.720 align:middle line:90%


00:06:13.720 --> 00:06:15.610 align:middle line:84%
>> On the other side
of the Pacific Ocean,

00:06:15.610 --> 00:06:18.220 align:middle line:84%
there's exciting evidence of
a civilization that could have

00:06:18.220 --> 00:06:22.010 align:middle line:90%
been lost in the cataclysm.

00:06:22.010 --> 00:06:25.500 align:middle line:84%
It lies off the most southerly
Japanese island of Yonaguni.

00:06:25.500 --> 00:06:31.500 align:middle line:90%


00:06:31.500 --> 00:06:35.820 align:middle line:84%
In 1997, reports reached me
of a mysterious underwater

00:06:35.820 --> 00:06:39.270 align:middle line:90%
structure.

00:06:39.270 --> 00:06:42.430 align:middle line:84%
Few geologists even know
about this new discovery.

00:06:42.430 --> 00:06:44.860 align:middle line:84%
It's been submerged
since sea levels rose

00:06:44.860 --> 00:06:46.169 align:middle line:90%
at the end of the Ice Age.

00:06:46.169 --> 00:06:51.800 align:middle line:90%


00:06:51.800 --> 00:06:54.560 align:middle line:84%
If these walls and
steps are man-made,

00:06:54.560 --> 00:06:57.004 align:middle line:84%
the story of civilization
is thousands of years

00:06:57.004 --> 00:06:57.920 align:middle line:90%
older than we thought.

00:06:57.920 --> 00:07:15.760 align:middle line:90%


00:07:15.760 --> 00:07:17.920 align:middle line:10%
To try to reach some
informed conclusions,

00:07:17.920 --> 00:07:20.330 align:middle line:10%
I set up an expedition
with a team of doctors,

00:07:20.330 --> 00:07:24.160 align:middle line:10%
including geologist Professor
Robert Schoch, and Egyptologist

00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:27.670 align:middle line:10%
John Anthony West.

00:07:27.670 --> 00:07:30.500 align:middle line:84%
>> There's just a tremendous
feeling of excitement to get

00:07:30.500 --> 00:07:33.550 align:middle line:84%
down there and see this
thing looming at you,

00:07:33.550 --> 00:07:36.580 align:middle line:84%
out of the cathedral
gloom at those depths.

00:07:36.580 --> 00:07:41.020 align:middle line:84%
There's a sense of the power
and the awe of the structure.

00:07:41.020 --> 00:07:44.260 align:middle line:10%
>> I'm starting to get a sense
of exactly what we're looking

00:07:44.260 --> 00:07:45.110 align:middle line:10%
at.

00:07:45.110 --> 00:07:47.710 align:middle line:90%
And it's just spectacular.

00:07:47.710 --> 00:07:51.460 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how to
judge it at the moment.

00:07:51.460 --> 00:07:54.050 align:middle line:84%
>> There's a mood of urgency,
because we have to complete

00:07:54.050 --> 00:07:56.204 align:middle line:84%
our work before the
current gets too strong.

00:07:56.204 --> 00:08:04.568 align:middle line:90%


00:08:04.568 --> 00:08:07.028 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING JAPANESE]

00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:12.440 align:middle line:90%


00:08:12.440 --> 00:08:15.650 align:middle line:84%
>> A local shark fisherman
diving for hammerheads

00:08:15.650 --> 00:08:18.380 align:middle line:84%
discovered this extraordinary
structure 10 years ago.

00:08:18.380 --> 00:08:21.980 align:middle line:90%


00:08:21.980 --> 00:08:25.400 align:middle line:84%
It's the height of
a six story building

00:08:25.400 --> 00:08:27.160 align:middle line:84%
and the length of
Egypt's Great Pyramid.

00:08:27.160 --> 00:08:30.080 align:middle line:90%


00:08:30.080 --> 00:08:32.539 align:middle line:84%
The islanders are convinced
it's an ancient monument.

00:08:32.539 --> 00:08:37.360 align:middle line:90%


00:08:37.360 --> 00:08:39.010 align:middle line:90%
Look at this peculiar trench.

00:08:39.010 --> 00:08:40.750 align:middle line:84%
It cuts through
from east to west.

00:08:40.750 --> 00:08:58.840 align:middle line:90%


00:08:58.840 --> 00:09:01.660 align:middle line:84%
The whole structure feels
designed and organized,

00:09:01.660 --> 00:09:03.240 align:middle line:90%
a work of intelligence.

00:09:03.240 --> 00:09:25.780 align:middle line:90%


00:09:25.780 --> 00:09:28.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm excited to find
these deep, round holes.

00:09:28.990 --> 00:09:30.880 align:middle line:84%
They look at the
seatings for large posts.

00:09:30.880 --> 00:09:36.860 align:middle line:90%


00:09:36.860 --> 00:09:40.730 align:middle line:84%
>> It was so interesting to note
a narrow trench about so wide

00:09:40.730 --> 00:09:43.070 align:middle line:84%
and so deep, which runs
perfectly straight for, I would

00:09:43.070 --> 00:09:47.210 align:middle line:84%
