of 60, 70 meters.

00:09:47.210 --> 00:09:49.040 align:middle line:84%
And off to the side
of that, there's

00:09:49.040 --> 00:09:53.090 align:middle line:84%
an indented area, again
with very precise cuts

00:09:53.090 --> 00:09:56.930 align:middle line:84%
along the side of it, which I
suppose they could be natural,

00:09:56.930 --> 00:09:59.960 align:middle line:84%
but I find it hard to
believe they are natural.

00:09:59.960 --> 00:10:04.317 align:middle line:10%
>> It's more spectacular than
anything nature produces, yes,

00:10:04.317 --> 00:10:06.650 align:middle line:10%
on the scale of the Grand
Canyon or something like that.

00:10:06.650 --> 00:10:07.900 align:middle line:90%
Nature does a pretty good job.

00:10:07.900 --> 00:10:13.480 align:middle line:84%
But the angles and planes and
complexity of it gives you--

00:10:13.480 --> 00:10:14.430 align:middle line:90%
it's awesome.

00:10:14.430 --> 00:10:15.230 align:middle line:90%
It really is.

00:10:15.230 --> 00:10:18.500 align:middle line:84%
>> There's two huge
circular holes in the rock,

00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:22.050 align:middle line:84%
